subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks
. 

L. fuscovittatus

is distinguished by the yellow scape and pedicel, long wide flagellum (
Fig. 3
), proboscis with apex flattened dorsally, awl-shaped, the dark pleura and coxae, hyaline wings (
Fig. 30
), and combined characters of the terminalia (
Figs. 31–40
).
